OL,3,CRemembering Shildon Works 40 years
OL,4,Csince devastating closure
OL,6,FForty years ago Shildon Works closed -
OL,7,Fleaving the region without one of its
OL,8,Fbiggest and most important industrial
OL,9,Fgiants.
OL,11,FThe town's wagon works sprang up just
OL,12,Fyears after the world's first
OL,13,Fpassenger train made its historic
OL,14,Fjourney through Shildon in 1825.
OL,16,FAt its height, the works employed
OL,17,Fnearly 3,000 people but it closed in
OL,18,F1984 - ending 151 years of production.
OL,20,FNearly 2,700 men lost their jobs,
OL,21,Fdevastating the town.
