OL,3,CRemembering Shildon Works 40 years
OL,4,Csince devastating closure
OL,6,FJohn Tomlin, 97, was just 14 when he
OL,7,Fstarted working there, following in
OL,8,Fthe footsteps of his grandfather - who
OL,9,Fwas chief clerk and has a street in
OL,10,FShildon named after him - father and
OL,11,Funcles.
OL,13,F"I started on the 10 February 1941,"
OL,14,Fhe said. "I was 14 and a half. My
OL,15,Ffather was foreman electrician. It was
OL,16,Fa place where family worked.
OL,18,F"It was a big part of my life. It was
OL,19,Fa big part of everybody's life here."
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/8
