OL,6,FDulcie Stobbs also worked there, like
OL,7,Fher mother, who was one of the women
OL,8,Fdrafted in to replace men who had gone
OL,9,Fto fight in the Second World War.
OL,11,F"My sister and me put our names down
OL,12,Fand we joined there," she said. "I was
OL,13,Fonly 16.
OL,15,F"Oh, I liked it. There were some good
OL,16,Fmen there, you know, and I never heard
OL,17,Fany bad language. And that's how I met
OL,18,Fmy boyfriend, my husband."
