OL,6,FHer husband Dennis added: "I was about
OL,7,Fthe last one to come out of Shildon
OL,8,FWorks.
OL,10,F"We were like one big family."
OL,12,FRail wagons were built in Shildon from
OL,13,F1833. It meant for the first time,
OL,14,Fhuge quantities of coal mined in
OL,15,Fnearby pits could be transported more
OL,16,Fquickly than ever.
OL,18,FIt made the horse and cart redundant,
OL,19,Fand the North East an industrial
OL,20,Fpioneer.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G4/8
