OL,3,CRemembering Shildon Works 40 years
OL,4,Csince devastating closure
OL,6,FDr Thomas Spain, from the National
OL,7,FRailway Museum, said: "Anything from
OL,8,Fumbrella handles to jam jars would
OL,9,Fhave gone by rail and also raw
OL,10,Fmaterials for industry that fed into
OL,11,Fthe steelworks on Teesside, Port
OL,12,FTalbot in South Wales and everywhere
OL,13,Fin between.
OL,15,F"It was an enormous contribution to
OL,16,FBritain's economic success. It was
OL,17,Fvery much the motorway, the artery of
OL,18,FBritish industry."
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G5/8
