OL,4,Csince devastating closure
OL,6,FHe added: "So it had this very long
OL,7,Flifetime but things started to change.
OL,8,FIt was very much how the economy was
OL,9,Fchanging towards a more road transport
OL,10,Fbased economy. Railways were quite
OL,11,Fcumbersome. Sending goods by rail was
OL,12,Flabour intensive."
OL,14,FDemand fell and in 1984 the works
OL,15,Fclosed, despite them still making a
OL,16,Fprofit at the time.
OL,18,FForty years later, people in Shildon
OL,19,Fstill feel its loss.
